Features

Features are the input variables used by the model to make predictions. They represent the characteristics of the data.
Example: In house price prediction—size, location, number of rooms

Label / Target

The label (or target) is the output variable the model is trying to predict.
Example: House price

Model

A model is a mathematical function or algorithm that maps inputs (features) to outputs (predictions). It learns patterns during training.

Training


Training is the process where the model learns from data by adjusting its parameters to minimize errors.
